Subject: [slayzone] =?UTF-8?q?slayzone:=20Phase=208.5=20followup=20?=
 =?UTF-8?q?=E2=80=94=20RegionData=20install=20before=20LoadInitialURL?=
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

Post-smoke: home-panel WebView's RegionData was attached AFTER
LoadInitialURL, but BindInterface can fire on navigation commit
(SlayzoneAutomationsUI::BindInterface calls FromRegionWebContents →
nullptr → binder bails → getSnapshot promise hangs forever).

Fix: attach RegionData immediately after creating the WebView, using
views::WebView::GetWebContents() which lazy-creates contents when
none exist (webview.h:97-99). Also re-check post-navigation as
defense in depth.

Validated via CDP probe: BindInterface now resolves view + host
non-null; Mojo pipe binds; automations snapshot round-trips via
sidecar. No functional changes outside SetHomePanel.
---
 .../ui/views/frame/slayzone_browser_view.cc   | 27 ++++++++++++++-----
 1 file changed, 20 insertions(+), 7 deletions(-)

diff --git a/chrome/browser/ui/views/frame/slayzone_browser_view.cc b/chrome/browser/ui/views/frame/slayzone_browser_view.cc
index 73b370766c722..3768e7607f0e9 100644
--- a/chrome/browser/ui/views/frame/slayzone_browser_view.cc
+++ b/chrome/browser/ui/views/frame/slayzone_browser_view.cc
@@ -165,19 +165,32 @@ bool SlayzoneBrowserView::SetHomePanel(std::string_view panel_id) {
     auto webview_owned = std::make_unique<views::WebView>(browser()->profile());
     home_panel_webview_ = AddChildView(std::move(webview_owned));
     home_panel_webview_->SetBoundsRect(GetLocalBounds());
-    // Phase 8.5 — give the home WebContents a RegionData back-pointer so
-    // the per-BrowserView Mojo binders (SlayzoneAutomationsUI etc.) can
-    // resolve via `FromRegionWebContents` exactly as region WebContents do.
-    // Installed before the first navigation so the BindInterface path
-    // triggered by the initial page load finds the host. Re-installed on
-    // every panel swap below since SetWebContents may cycle contents.
+  }
+
+  // Phase 8.5 — install RegionData BEFORE navigation. LoadInitialURL
+  // triggers the WebUI BindInterface path which looks up
+  // FromRegionWebContents; if RegionData isn't on the contents by then
+  // the binder bails and the panel's Mojo host never gets a receiver
+  // (symptom: sidecar sees no `<panel>:get-snapshot` traffic, the React
+  // empty-state sticks). `GetWebContents()` on views::WebView lazy-
+  // creates contents, so the ptr is valid after this call.
+  if (content::WebContents* contents = home_panel_webview_->GetWebContents()) {
+    if (!RegionData::FromWebContents(contents)) {
+      RegionData::CreateForWebContents(contents, this);
+    }
   }
 
   const std::string url =
       base::StrCat({"chrome://slayzone-", panel_id, "/"});
   home_panel_webview_->LoadInitialURL(GURL(url));
+  // Re-check RegionData post-navigation in case WebView cycled the
+  // contents pointer during LoadInitialURL (first-load creates contents;
+  // GetWebContents() pre-navigation already triggered creation so this
+  // is mostly defensive).
   if (content::WebContents* contents = home_panel_webview_->GetWebContents()) {
-    RegionData::CreateForWebContents(contents, this);
+    if (!RegionData::FromWebContents(contents)) {
+      RegionData::CreateForWebContents(contents, this);
+    }
   }
   home_panel_webview_->SetBoundsRect(GetLocalBounds());
   home_panel_webview_->SetVisible(true);
